This page is a supplementary teaching scaffold for JavaScript lowering.

## Core concept

A lowerer converts selected validated HIR into target code while preserving language semantics that JavaScript does not enforce by itself.

## Beanstalk boundary

JavaScript lowering receives an explicit selected function set and link plan.

It:

- emits only selected functions
- emits required helpers only
- maps stable binding identities to runtime imports
- preserves checked numeric, cast, map and formatting semantics
- consumes the external glue plan supplied by project assembly

HTML page assembly, route selection and fragment order belong to the HTML builder.

## Rewrite focus

Explain semantic gaps between source language and host language, demand-driven helper emission and why source imports are absent from a backend.

Canonical details live in both architecture authorities.
